{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "12", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "18", "M": "46", "S": "40"}}, "news": [{"title": "Relief for Bhimrao Bada residents as Telangana HC orders 2BHK houses, ends 17-year dispute", "para": "The Telangana high court has ordered the state government to provide 2BHK houses. This decision brings closure to a seventeen-year legal battle for displaced families. Residents were evicted after their slum status was withdrawn in two thousand eight. The court directed allotments in Kollur within two months of receiving the order. Legal heirs of deceased petitioners will also be considered for these new homes.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/telangana-high-courts-historic-ruling-grants-2bhk-homes-to-bhimrao-bada-slum-residents-ending-17-year-dispute/132341869?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-116249/132341869.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Architects association urge Ranchi civic body to end building plan approval deadlock", "para": "Licensed technical professionals in Jharkhand are concerned about building map approval delays.  Many property owners face rejections despite obtaining holding numbers.  The association argues these rejections contradict established building bye-laws.  They urge the municipal commissioner to expedite map approvals for valid holding holders.  A meeting is planned to discuss these ongoing issues in detail.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/ranchi-architects-demand-resolution-to-building-plan-approval-delays/132341855?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-776130/132341855.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Renting a house in Chandigarh likely to soon go fully digital", "para": "Chandigarh administration has proposed new digital tenancy rules for registration and dispute resolution.  These rules aim to create a fully online framework for all rental agreements.  Landlords and tenants must submit tenancy details via a dedicated online portal.  The proposed system will establish a digital repository for all tenancy records.  These rules will become operational after public objections and potential court decisions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/technology/chandigarh-set-to-go-fully-digital-for-house-rentals/132341819?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-838966/132341819.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "technology"}]}